<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-1504] HTTP_URI and HTTP_PATH message headers not concatenated when sending messages to http endpoint</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-1504</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a message is sent to an http endpoint, the path specified in the HTTP_PATH header is ignored.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the HttpProducer.createMethod() of the camel-http component, the URI is taken from the HTTP_URI header or the endpoint, but the HTTP_PATH header is not concatenated. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See also the discussion on the mailing list: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Setting-a-path-in-message-header-with-Camel-http-2.0M1-td22781504.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Setting-a-path-in-message-header-with-Camel-http-2.0M1-td22781504.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
